"The main stream of the Yangtze River has achieved full coverage of water-based green comprehensive service areas - Xinhua News" 
"The Chongqing Fuling Water-based Green Comprehensive Service Area was officially put into operation on December 10 as scheduled, which is the second water-based green comprehensive service area in the upper reaches of the Yangtze River after the Sichuan Luzhou Water-based Green Comprehensive Service Area was put into operation on the 8th. Xinhua News, Wuhan, December 11th, reporter Wang Xian
"Thus, the water-based green comprehensive service areas have covered the upper, middle, and lower reaches of the Yangtze River." 
"Qiu Jianhua, deputy director of the Yangtze River Navigation Management Bureau of the Ministry of Transportation, introduced that before this, 10 water-based green comprehensive service areas have been built and operated in the middle and lower reaches of the Yangtze River in provinces such as Hubei, Hunan, Jiangxi, Anhui, and Jiangsu, which have been recognized by the majority of sailors and played an important role in promoting the high-quality development of Yangtze River navigation." 
"The full coverage of water-based green comprehensive service areas is another milestone in the construction of green navigation on the Yangtze River, and the ability to receive ship-borne pollutants and provide navigation services has been significantly improved."
According to the introduction, the water-based green comprehensive service area is an important facility for providing all-around production and life services for a large number of ships and crew members, helping to solve the problem of "urgent distress and anticipation".
The two water-based green comprehensive service areas in the upper reaches of the Yangtze River that have been built and put into operation integrate life services, production services, and government services, with a green and environmentally friendly theme, and with ship maintenance and ship emergency rescue services as the main features. It realizes the "one-time mooring and multiple services" for ships within the port, which will make the work of the crew members who navigate the Yangtze River all year round more efficient and life more convenient.